# Getting Started

## Welcome

This guide walks new organizations through their initial Atlas CertOps deployment.

Most organizations complete initial setup in less than one hour.

---

# Step 1 — Accept Your Invitation

Your organization administrator will provide an invitation link.

Select **Accept Invitation**.

Create your password or authenticate using your organization's Single Sign-On provider.

---

# Step 2 — Sign In

Navigate to:

https://app.certops.atlasandelse.com

Enter your credentials.

After successful authentication you will arrive at the Dashboard.

---

# Step 3 — Complete Your Profile

Open:

Settings → My Profile

Review:

- Name
- Email
- Time Zone
- Notification Preferences

Save your changes.

---

# Step 4 — Review Your Dashboard

The dashboard displays:

- Expiring Certificates
- Recently Updated Records
- Pending Approvals
- Assigned Tasks
- Compliance Health
- Recent Activity

---

# Step 5 — Create Your First Certificate

Navigate to:

Certificates

Select:

New Certificate

Complete all required fields.

Typical fields include:

- Certificate Name
- Certificate Type
- Owner
- Issue Date
- Expiration Date
- Renewal Interval
- Department
- Notes

Upload any supporting documentation.

Select Save.

---

# Step 6 — Verify Notifications

Navigate to:

Settings → Notifications

Confirm:

Email Notifications

Renewal Alerts

Assignment Alerts

Approval Requests

Digest Frequency

---

# Step 7 — Invite Team Members

Navigate to:

Administration → Users

Select:

Invite User

Assign an appropriate role.

Examples include:

Administrator

Compliance Manager

Supervisor

Viewer

Operator

Users receive an email invitation immediately.

---

# Step 8 — Import Existing Data

Navigate to:

Administration → Imports

Supported formats:

CSV

Excel (.xlsx)

Follow the Import Wizard.

Resolve any validation errors before finalizing the import.

---

# Step 9 — Configure Approval Workflows

Navigate to:

Administration → Workflows

Create approval chains based on organizational requirements.

Example:

Employee
↓

Supervisor
↓

Compliance Officer
↓

Final Approval

---

# Step 10 — Begin Managing Compliance

Your organization is now ready to manage certifications using Atlas CertOps.

Continue with the User Guide for detailed workflows.

